# Zentivra вЂ“ Frontier AI Radar: Implementation Plan

A daily multi-agent intelligence system that tracks competitor releases, foundation model updates, AI research publications, and HuggingFace benchmarks вЂ” then produces an executive + technical PDF digest delivered by email.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys Needed** (you can provide these when we reach each phase):
> 1. **LLM API Key** вЂ” Pick ONE (recommend **Google Gemini** for cost-efficiency):
>    - Google Gemini API key, **OR**
>    - OpenAI API key, **OR**
>    - Anthropic Claude API key
> 2. **Email Delivery** вЂ” Pick ONE:
>    - **SendGrid API key** (recommended, free tier = 100 emails/day), **OR**
>    - SMTP credentials (Gmail app password, or any SMTP server)
> 3. **Optional but recommended:**
>    - Semantic Scholar API key (free, speeds up research queries)
>    - HuggingFace API token (free, avoids rate limits on HF API)

> [!WARNING]
> **Software to Install on Your Laptop** (before we start coding):
> 1. **PostgreSQL 16+** вЂ” [Download here](https://www.postgresql.org/downloads/) вЂ” our primary database
> 2. **Node.js 20+ LTS** вЂ” [Download here](https://nodejs.org/) вЂ” for the Next.js frontend
> 3. **Python 3.11+** вЂ” likely already installed (we'll verify)
> 4. **Optional:** Docker Desktop вЂ” if you prefer running PostgreSQL as a container instead of installing natively

> [!CAUTION]
> **Key Design Decisions for Your Approval:**
> 1. **LLM Provider**: Recommend **Google Gemini 2.0 Flash** (cheapest, fast, good quality). Alternative: OpenAI GPT-4o-mini. Which do you prefer?
> 2. **Orchestration**: Using **APScheduler** (lightweight, no external infra) instead of Prefect/Dagster/Temporal (which need separate servers). Good for our scale.
> 3. **Frontend**: **Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS** for the web UI (spec suggests this). OK?
> 4. **PDF Engine**: **WeasyPrint** (renders HTML/CSS to PDF, beautiful output). Requires installing `GTK` runtime on Windows вЂ” I'll guide you through it.

---

## Tech Stack (Final)

| Layer | Technology | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Backend API** | Python 3.11+ / FastAPI | Async, fast, great for agents |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL 16 | Relational, JSONB for flexible findings |
| **ORM** | SQLAlchemy 2.0 + Alembic | Migrations, async support |
| **Task Queue** | APScheduler | Lightweight scheduler, no infra needed |
| **Crawler** | httpx (async) + Playwright (JS fallback) | Handles static + dynamic pages |
| **Extraction** | BeautifulSoup4, trafilatura, feedparser | HTML/RSS/Atom parsing |
| **LLM** | Google Gemini API (via `google-genai`) | Summarization, ranking, narrative |
| **Embeddings** | sentence-transformers (local) | Dedup similarity, clustering |
| **PDF** | WeasyPrint | HTMLв†’PDF with CSS styling |
| **Email** | SendGrid SDK or smtplib | Delivery |
| **Frontend** | Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS | Modern, fast UI |
| **Observability** | Python `logging` + structlog | Structured JSON logs |

